In a large bowl, combine the sausage, onion, chives, basil, garlic, 3/4 of the paprika, salt and pepper. Unfold pastry onto a lightly floured surface. Roll each pastry sheet into an 11-in. x 10-1/2-in. rectangle. Cut widthwise into 3-1/2-in. strips.
Spread 1/2 cup of sausage mixture down the center of each strip. Fold pastry over and press edges together to seal. Cut each roll into six pieces.
Place seam side down on a rack in a shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with remaining paprika. Bake at 350Â° for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.
